Meet <b>Burns Jerome</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Jerome has lived in his modest digs at <a href='/home/?user=sangan28'>31272 Union Avenue</a> in Metro Park since July 17th, 2006. When he's not reading comic books or playing games, Jerome is probably on a board. It could be any type of board really. <br><br>He's won trophies for the Snowboard Slalom, Kai's Surfari, and the Peabody Park Half Pipe. It's a wonder he found room for all 22 of his trophies in his Room of Success. What else would you expect a room holding that many trophies to be called?<br><br>When you're done admiring Jerome's achievements, you can hang out in his Family Room completely equipped Vintage Dome Hockey Games. If you think you're seeing things, you may want to do a double take. No need to be alarmed, it's probably just his trusty hologram projectors. <br><br>If you happen to snoop around, you may happen to discover Jerome's den of privacy, which is more like a treasure chest than a den. Luckily for Jerome, all of the Pirates were run out of Millsberry back in the 1800's.<br><br>If it's a nice afternoon, maybe you'll be able to hang out in his Yard of Parties. The slip and slide is fully functional, so be sure to bring your swimsuit. If you're more of a sit and watch type, you'll be able to get a great view of all the action from Jerome's tree house. <br><br>The next time you cross paths with Jerome, make sure to congratulate him and thank him on being such a great citizen to the town of Millsberry.<br><br></div>
